This was a tricky backport because of the difference between master and 7.x due to type removal.
Here we used to check the type names are all the same. I decided to simplify this bit by removing this validation. It is not really a meaningful validation. The reason is that in 7.x each index may only contain a single type. While it is possible for 6.x indices to have differently named types, as long as their mappings do not conflict we should be fine.
@droberts195 As this is the main difference compared to the PR in master, could you verify this makes sense to you too?

